      "text": "👍 A woman wanted for a murder that took place in Cariacica, Espírito Santo, was arrested in Boston, in the United States, on the 13th. Kele Cristian Alves Pereira, 38, from Minas Gerais, worked as a cleaner in the country and had her identity discovered after being suspected of stealing credit cards. The information was released by reporter Thathyanno Desa, from the Gnews USA website, and replicated by Brazilian portals abroad.\n\nAccording to the site, Kele introduced himself as \"Kelly Cristian\". On January 2, 2026, after cleaning, a customer noticed the disappearance of credit cards. Then unauthorized purchases were made at a supermarket in Massachusetts. The victim reported losses of approximately $2,500 (about R$13,000).\n\nFrom the suspicion of theft, Kele's true identity was discovered. She was detained as she left a supermarket and awaits developments from the local courts, in addition to possible extradition to Brazil.",
      "text_resolved": "👍 A woman wanted for a murder that took place in Cariacica, Espírito Santo, was arrested in Boston, in the United States, on the 13th. Kele Cristian Alves Pereira, 38, from Minas Gerais, worked as a cleaner in the country and had her identity discovered after being suspected of stealing credit cards. The information was released by reporter Thathyanno Desa, from the Gnews USA website, and replicated by Brazilian portals abroad.\n\nAccording to the site, Kele introduced himself as \"Kelly Cristian\". On January 2, 2026, after cleaning, a customer noticed the disappearance of credit cards. Then unauthorized purchases were made at a supermarket in Massachusetts. The victim reported losses of approximately $2,500 (about R$13,000).\n\nFrom the suspicion of theft, Kele's true identity was discovered. She was detained as she left a supermarket and awaits developments from the local courts, in addition to possible extradition to Brazil.",
